<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin 
<emphasis box="[485,560,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">aureus</emphasis>
(gold) and 
<emphasis box="[701,777,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">ventris</emphasis>
(venter) due to the coloration of the integument reddish brown-gold on the apical area of terga and sterna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,2015]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,575]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1916,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[342,577,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[342,577,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Xylocopa auriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[583,645,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[583,645,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is also within the historical concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[1081,1219,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis box="[1081,1219,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, F." pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="247 - 302" refId="ref34236" refString="Smith, F. (1874) Monograph of the genus Xylocopa Latr. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 22, 247 - 302. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00168. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Smith (1874)</bibRefCitation>
when he described that species based on a female from Tefé, 
<collectingCountry box="[930,1001,1952,1978]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, as was denoted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lucia, M. &amp; Gonzalez, V. H." pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="31 - 48" refId="ref32050" refString="Lucia, M. &amp; Gonzalez, V. H. (2017) New species and designation of primary types in Neotropical carpenter bees of the genus Xylocopa Latreille (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 61, 31 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / jhr. 61.20345" type="journal article" year="2017">Lucia &amp; Gonzalez (2017)</bibRefCitation>
when described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lucia &amp; Gonzalez" authorityYear="2017" box="[419,556,1988,2014]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbarae">
<emphasis box="[419,556,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">X. barbarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species share the same labrum shape, similar body size and punctation on vertex and metasoma, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[487,642,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[487,504,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[519,642,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">auriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[650,714,153,179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[650,714,153,179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs by the reddish brown-gold area on metasomal discs and by the whitish pubescence on face, gena, disc of T4 and lateral sides of T3–T5 (pubescence and integument mostly black in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[248,386,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis box="[248,386,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
The exemplars of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[406,545,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis box="[406,545,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that we examined in foreign collections are consistent in their features and all occur in the Amazonian region (Boreal Brazilian dominion 
<emphasis box="[820,882,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morrone, J. J." box="[889,1063,297,323]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref32894" refString="Morrone, J. J. (2014) Biogeographical regionalisation of the Neotropical region. Zootaxa, 3782, 1 - 110. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3782.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Morrone, 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The single specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">X. auriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[233,295,333,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[233,295,333,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was collected in a locality of the Andean region (Pacific dominion) at approximately 
<specimenCount box="[1241,1321,333,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1241,1318,333,359]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="m" value="900.0">900 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
a.s.l. More specimens need to be collected to identify variations and describe the male of this new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Another species that has similarities with this new species by the whitish hairs on face and lateral sides of T3–T5 is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[177,275,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electa">
<emphasis box="[177,194,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[208,275,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">electa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[473,588,441,467]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[643,711,441,467]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[726,878,441,467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" pagination="1802" refId="ref33007" refString="Moure, J. S. (2012) Xylocopini Latreille, 1802. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba. Online version. Available from: http: // www. moure. cria. org. br / catalogue (accessed 15 January 2020)" type="book chapter" year="2012">Moure, 2012</bibRefCitation>
). A female 
<typeStatus box="[1004,1091,441,467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">syntype</typeStatus>
of this latter species deposited in NHMUK was examined and it is noticeably different from 
<taxonomicName authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[842,996,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[842,859,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[873,996,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">auriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1003,1065,477,503]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1003,1065,477,503]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, mainly by the smaller body size (body length~17, mesosoma width~6.5), integument of head and mesosoma mostly black with weak highlights, labrum with three well-defined tubercles, hyaline wings and punctation on discs of metasomal terga sparser.
</paragraph>
